<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5905871-tony"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1317931258i/5905871._CR0,4,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5905871-tony">Tony</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Hersey himself published &quot;Hiroshima: The Aftermath. Survivors’ stories.&quot;<br/>in the July 15, 1985 issue of The New Yorker Magazine (the same magazine that <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Hersey himself published "Hiroshima: The Aftermath. Survivors’ stories."<br />in the July 15, 1985 issue of The New Yorker Magazine (the same magazine that published his watershed "Hiroshima" in the Aug. 24, 1946 issue). <br /><br />The magazine has kindly placed the entire text of this follow-up online (together with Hersey's original 1946 reporting): <br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/1985/07/15/hiroshima-the-aftermath">https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/19...</a><br /><br />Also see:<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/1946/08/31/hiroshima">https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/19...</a><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
